cs.AR, cs.PF, cs.DC, cs.MS, cs.NA 

Reasoning: 
- cs.AR (Hardware Architecture): The paper focuses on developing an asymmetry-aware implementation of the BLAS for AMPs, which involves designing hardware architecture for efficient parallelization and workload distribution. 
- cs.PF (Performance): The paper evaluates the performance of the developed implementation and compares it with the legacy version of LAPACK, which falls under the performance category. 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing): The paper discusses parallelization strategies for distributing workload among different types of cores in AMPs, which falls under the distributed and parallel computing category. 
- cs.MS (Mathematical Software): The paper deals with the implementation of mathematical software libraries (BLAS and LAPACK) for AMPs, which falls under the mathematical software category. 
- cs.NA (Numerical Analysis): The paper discusses the numerical tools provided by dense linear algebra libraries and their relevance in scientific and engineering applications, which falls under the numerical analysis category.
